        <div n="160-36L-" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the Year 1712.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">A</hi><hi rend="underline">TLAS</hi>, we read in antient Song,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-2"> Was so exceeding tall and strong,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-3"> He bore the Skies upon his Back,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-4"> Just as a Pedlar does his Pack:</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-5"> But as a Pedlar overprest,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-6"> Unloads upon a Stall to rest;</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-7"> Or, when he can no longer stand,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-8"> Desires a Friend to lend a Hand;</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-9"> So <hi rend="underline">Atlas</hi>, lest the pond'rous Spheres</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-10"> Should sink, and fall about his Ears;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-11"> Got <hi rend="underline">Hercules</hi> to bear the Pile,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-12"> That he might sit and rest a while.Yet <hi rend="underline">Hercules</hi> was not so strong,</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-13"> Nor could have born it half so long.Great Statesmen are in this Condition;</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-14"> And <hi rend="underline">Atlas</hi> is a Politician;</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-15"> A <hi rend="underline">premier</hi> Minister of State;<hi rend="underline">Alcides</hi> one of second Rate.</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-16"> Suppose then <hi rend="underline">Atlas</hi> ne'er so wise,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-17"> Yet when the Weight of Kingdoms lies</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-18"> Too long, upon his single Shoulders,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-160-36L--line-19"> Sink down he must, or find <hi rend="underline">Upholders</hi>.</l></lg></div>
